The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal
 Wednesday, March 31, 2004 				 Life for abduction
																								Purulia, March 30: Three accused in the Naresh Agarwal abduction case were today sentenced to life imprisonment by a fast track court here.																								Main accused Gopal Gupta, Agarwals driver Sahadeb Kundu and an electrician in the industrialists company, Suresh Prasad, were handed the punishment by additional sessions judge of fast-track court II Asha Arora.																								Jhalda-based Agarwal, the managing director of a downstream unit of Haldia Petrochemicals, was abducted along with his driver in April while travelling to Durgapur. He was released 12 days later for a secret ransom of Rs 32 lakh.																								Two prime accused, including Hajipur MLA Rama Singh of Bihar, escaped the sentence as they are absconding. 
